1. Mi smo se *borili* protiv nepravde. (We fought against injustice.)
2. Oni su se *borili* do poslednjeg daha. (They fought until their last breath.)
3. Ja ću se *boriti* za svoja prava. (I will fight for my rights.)
4. *Borili* smo se sa teškom situacijom. (We struggled with a difficult situation.)
5. Ti si se *borio* protiv neprijatelja. (You fought against the enemy.)
6. Ona se *borila* sa bolešću godinama. (She fought with the illness for years.)
7. Deca su se *borila* za prvo mesto na takmičenju. (The children competed for the first place in the competition.)
8. *Borite* se za ono u šta verujete. (Fight for what you believe in.)
9. Vi ste se *borili* hrabro u ratu. (You fought bravely in the war.)
10. Oni će se *boriti* za svoju slobodu. (They will fight for their freedom.)

(Note: In Serbian, the verb "boriti se" means "to fight" or "to struggle". The word "borili" is the past tense form of the verb "boriti se", while "borio" is the masculine singular past tense form, and "borila" is the feminine singular past tense form. "Borite" is the imperative form, which is used for giving commands or orders.)